Description: AudioCubes.com (or AC for short) is Internet's premier source for the latest electronics, gadgets, and toys from Japan.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: AudioCubes.com (or AC for short) is Internet's premier source for the latest electronics, gadgets, and toys from Japan. Our retail brand AC Gears is located in the heart of Greenwich Village, New York City. Currently AudioCubes.com is the only online retailer that is sanctioned by Audio-Technica Japan and Elecom Japan to sell their domestic Japanese electronics and accessories online to consumers outside of Japan. AudioCubes.com was founded in 2001 in Boston, and was one of the first online retailers that made Japanese consumer electronics available worldwide outside of Japan. Within one year, AudioCubes expanded from consumer end goods to include high fidelity audio gear. By 2002, Audio Cubes Inc established AudioCubes2.com (AC2) to accommodate the increase in demand for high end audiophile electronics and accessories. AC2 has since then become a force of its own in making high end Japanese audio gear and accessories available worldwide. In 2007, AudioCubes moved its headquarter to New York City, and openned AC Gears - an one-of-a-kind gadget store featuring both imported and domestically made electronics that are often unavailable beyond the Internet, or on the shelves of generic big box electronic stores. At the time when counterfeits and knockoffs are rampant on the Internet, AudioCubes sources only from the original manufacturers, even with higher costs, to ensure our customers receive the latest, genuine products from Japan. Even though our products are shipped out from Japan directly to you, AudioCubes Inc is a US company, so call or email us anytime if you have questions regarding your order. Don't hesitate to contact us if you have any questions or a particular product in mind that you can't seem to find anywhere else. Enjoy your shopping experience, and have fun treasure hunting in our high-end gadget land.

Description: The Jason Foundation, Inc. is a non-profit organization dedicated to the awareness and prevention of youth suicide.
Full Description: The Jason Foundation, Inc. (JFI) is dedicated to the prevention of the “Silent Epidemic” of youth suicide through educational and awareness programs that equip young people, educators/youth workers and parents with the tools and resources to help identify and assist at-risk youth. JFI believes that awareness and education are the first steps to prevention. They want to establish a Triangle of Prevention by providing students, parents and teachers the tools and resources to help identify and help at-risk youth. This is accomplished through a curriculum unit for students and informational seminars for teachers and parents. This instructional kit provides resources to accomplish this goal. The materials are easy to use and are intended to provide educational information. There is no intent to diagnose or treat suicidal ideation. JFI’s intention is to empower youth, educators and parents to help recognize when young people are in pain and know to get professional help involved as soon as possible. The Jason Foundation, Inc. is a non-profit 501c3.
